It's a cold, fall evening in the midwest. I'm in search of...soup! I stumbled across this recipe and, I'm pleased to say, it hit the spot. I did A LOT of substituting (sweet potato for squash, some kidney beans for the a portion of the chickpeas, etc.) but it still came out tasty! Great combination of flavors and super healthy. The chili was a bit thick and the next time I make it I think I'll try some chicken broth instead. Happy cooking!

