This is my favorite chile recipe by far. This serves as a good base recipe from which substitutions can be made. We put in lots of summer squash and fresh corn. We only used two 19-oz cans of beans - one chickpea, one kidney - and substituted one can of tomatoes for the fresh. Grate some fresh parmesan over the bowls. Very yummy!

