Rating: 2
This wasn't my idea of a chili - just a lightly spiced vegetable stew. The vegetables lost their texture due to all being cooked for an hour, & the flavour of the fresh herbs was largely lost due to being added at the beginning. It could be improved greatly by cooking for less time & adding the herbs towards the end, but would still not be as rich a chili as those versions (whether meat or vegetarian) that use chocolate, beer, ancho chillies etc - the style that I prefer.

Rating: 2
We were not as impressed as all the previous reviewers. I followed the recipe to the letter and made no modifications. The taste/texture/appearance were not bad, just certainly not a 3 or 4 fork meal. I can't see putting this one on a "got-to-have-it" list for another day. Note after I wrote the first note - I decided to brown about 1/4 pound ground beef with some onions and add that to the vegetarian stew. Made it much better - I guess I just like the meat!

